# Terraform / AWS / containers

- Optimize the initial architecture for fewer than 100 users and low idle cost.
- Prefer managed services only when their operational benefit justifies fixed cost.
- Avoid introducing EKS, MSK, NAT Gateway, ElastiCache, or always-on multi-AZ resources without a documented requirement and cost estimate.
- Pin provider/module versions according to repository policy.
- Keep state remote, encrypted, locked, and separate by environment.
- Never commit secrets or sensitive tfvars.
- IAM must use least privilege; avoid wildcard actions/resources unless justified.
- Encrypt data at rest and in transit.
- Add log retention and cost tags.
- Expose outputs deliberately; mark sensitive outputs.
- Docker images should use multi-stage builds, non-root runtime users, minimal bases, health checks, and pinned major versions.
- Run format, validate, and configured static/security checks.
- For changes that may increase monthly cost, include a brief cost-impact note.
